{:metadata {:description [{"text" "<p>This entry includes Bul1, Bul2, Bsc5 and YNR068C from Saccharomyces cerevisiae and homologues from fungi. They are adaptor proteins that facilitate the ligase-substrate interaction. Bul1 binds the ubiquitin ligase Rsp5, via an N-terminal PPSY motif [[cite:PUB00009998]]. The complex containing Bul1 and Rsp5 is involved in intracellular trafficking of the general amino acid permease Gap1 [[cite:PUB00010116]], degradation of Rog1 in cooperation with Bul2 and GSK-3 [[cite:PUB00009999]], and mitochondrial inheritance [[cite:PUB00010000]]. Bul2, which is homologous to Bul1, also interacts with Rsp5 [[cite:PUB00009998]].</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Bul3p, the product of two adjacent open reading frames (Bsc5 and YNR068C) separated by a stop codon that undergoes readthrough translation. BUL3 is involved in ubiquitin-mediated sorting of plasma membrane proteins and interacts with WW domains of Rsp5 in vitro [[cite:PUB00089892]].</p>", "llm" false, "checked" false, "updated" false}], :is-reviewed-llm false, :representative-structure nil, :overlaps-with nil, :member-databases {"panther" {"PTHR31904" "BYPASS OF STOP CODON PROTEIN 5-RELATED"}}, :is-updated-llm false, :name {"name" "Bul1-like", "short" "Bul1-like"}, :wikipedia nil, :source-database "interpro", :type "family", :counters {"structures" 0, "domain_architectures" 0, "proteomes" 751, "taxa" 1953, "subfamilies" 0, "interactions" 0, "matches" 2333, "sets" 0, "proteins" 2333, "structural_models" {"alphafold" 1481}, "pathways" 0}, :integrated nil, :cross-references {}, :set-info nil, :accession "IPR039634", :literature {"PUB00010000" {"URL" nil, "issue" "6", "authors" ["Fisk HA" "Yaffe MP."], "ISO_journal" "J. Cell Biol.", "DOI_URL" "http://dx.doi.org/10.1083/jcb.145.6.1199", "medline_journal" "J Cell Biol", "title" "A role for ubiquitination in mitochondrial inheritance in Saccharomyces cerevisiae.", "year" 1999, "raw_pages" "1199-208", "volume" "145", "ISBN" nil, "PMID" 10366593}, "PUB00010116" {"